snippet.textDisplay:
Thanks for sharing this piece of your lives with us. I really enjoyed the experience of the trip and the chemistry between the two of you. You're both very charming! I loved the sharing of the legend of White Snake; it reminded me an anecdote with my dad (bless his soul).

When I was really young, I saw the movie version of the story and it freaked me out thinking there were snakes posing as humans. He dispel my fears by explaining that these were just stories, and they were a means to convey Chinese philosophy: "you won't forget this story easily, right?". Short version is that human and snake represent living beings who can be as different as can be. In the story, the couple demonstrated their love, loyalty and respect for each other. However a third party however well intention-ed, destroyed the marriage; doesn't matter that the monk used truth to do it. There are many small lessons in the story, such as being tolerant and respectful to others who are different. Between couples, don't just listen to others outside of the family unit; the family unit is most important and valuable. Just because someone is different (the snake in the case of the story), doesn't mean that they don't have love and humanity. I forget the rest.
